featured_reviews.review_id:
I got the Rose Oolong Peach Cake + Honeycomb Dalgona Latte and my friend got the Vanilla Strawberry Shortcake + Iced Shaken Lychee Black Tea.

I would highly recommend the rose peach cake as it's something I haven't been able to get anywhere else and it tasted divine! The rest was sweet and tasted exactly as expected, especially the strawberry cake and the lychee black tea. Not to make that sound bad, they're staples in every store for a reason (they never miss)!! Though, not going to lie, wasn't a huge fan of the honeycomb in my dalgona latte as it was too sweet and it was slightly unnerving every time I'd encounter its crunchy texture. Still drank it all, but probably wouldn't get it again...

Other than that, the decor was nice and clean and the atmosphere was quiet and serene. Also, it's a little on the expensive side... so definitely more of an experience than a regular hang-out spot. Hope the employees enjoyed the relaxing morning as it seemed like a slow shift (to be fair we went around brunch time on a Tuesday). Tldr, worth it to try the rose oolong peach cake and experience the fun of the stacking cake cups.

featured_reviews.review_id: Had a Minus Cup Combo of their Blueberry Lavender Slush and Earl Grey Toasted Milk Cake. It's nice that we're able to mix and match the cake/drink. The cake was refreshing and smooth with crunchy chocolate bites. The lavender flavour in the drink was strong, and I liked that it wasn't overpowered by the blueberry. The plastic cake cylinder snaps onto the drink lid for easy transport. The shop is clean with cute decor. It's a tad pricey so not your everyday treat, but they have unique flavours that warrant a trip back.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Please improve your packaging!

I have been longing for their roll cakes but they are sold out every time I went there after work. I finally am able to get their roll cake today.

During my time walking back home from the store (i.e. 5 minutes walk), the handle suddenly breaks and the whole cake drops onto the ground.  The cake is still edible but the cream and chocolate are all over the place. I did not swing the cake whatsoever but I am so disappointed that a $45-dollar cake has that weak packaging and cannot hold the cake for even 5 minutes under normal usage.

Hopefully the cake tastes good. If not, I am not going back again :(

featured_reviews.review_id:
I was new to coaching when I began working with Laura and have found the journey to be extremely gratifying in ways I could not have anticipated. Throughout the work we have done, Laura has displayed the utmost professionalism and genuine desire to help me realize my potential.

I thought coaching would be about spreadsheets and processes, but rather, the work has been centered on equipping me with a better understanding of myself, which is of far more value and use than any spreadsheet. In deciphering the mental shifts and habits that will bring me closer to my goals, I'm creating changes that will serve me for a lifetime.

Laura holds the space for these positive changes to come about. I highly recommend her.

I chose MJ Physio because they had a physiotherapist that could help with my concussion and it was close enough that I could walk to it with minimal symptoms. I'm so happy I found it and Krishna! I've been receiving concussion therapy for two months now and it's like I'm finally human again. I can walk, bike, and drive again, and my cognition and screen time tolerance is improving with the exercises. None of this was the case when I first started with Krishna.

During my first session, Krishna quickly identified that my vision was affected by the concussion and that is the likely cause of my symptoms. It was a huge relief to understand why I was feeling so yucky and have a plan to fix it. Thank you so much!!!

featured_reviews.review_id: Krishna treated my left hip bursitis and knee injury from golf, on 1st day of season. My pain was so bad I couldn't walk & completely bent over the next day and on. I should've gone to my doc for a shot(which I found out later), but a week later, I went to MJ physio. She used ultrasound & tens machine to help heal. She told me about certain exercises that I should do to strengthen & stretching my glutes & hamstrings, as I wasn't in good shape to play golf. Doc said it'd take 6-12 weeks, but I played my first golf 5 weeks after injury and I played better because I was more stronger in my core and glutes. I'm still getting treatments b'c of sore left shoulder & back and she's used shock therapy for shoulder and it has rapidly helped the shoulder. My back pain is also getting better. 6 weeks later now, I'm playing golf better & I can run if I have to, btw, I'm a newish senior. I'm planning to check in with Krishna from time to time if I feel aches & pains. Thanks much, Krishna!

featured_reviews.review_id: While the food was average, the breathtaking view and reasonable prices made it a worthwhile experience. The menu offered a variety of dishes, but they lacked that special something to make them truly memorable. However, the real star of the show was the panoramic view of the surrounding landscape. Watching the view while enjoying a reasonably priced meal was a delightful experience. If you're looking for a budget-friendly dining option with a stunning view, this place is worth a visit.

featured_reviews.review_id: We had our wedding reception brunch of about 60 people in the Skyline Room at Seasons in the Park restaurant in early August of 2023, and we were blown away by the outstanding service at our wedding! The food was delicious, the portions were generous, and the restaurant was more than happy to accommodate a few of our guests who had dietary restrictions. The service was fast, and the communication with us was incredible. So many of our guests also complimented the excellent service they received during our reception, and we had so many compliments about the beautiful view of Vancouver as well. The servers even went out of their way to ensure that we, the bride and groom, were comfortable and well taken care of during the entire brunch. Even the preplanning was smooth and seamless, and communicating back and forth with Makda about wedding details was an easy process. Many of our guests have commented that this was one of the best weddings they've been to, and we could not have done it without all the wonderful help provided by Seasons. As a wedding venue, we highly recommend Seasons in the Park! Plus, we felt compared to other wedding venues, that Seasons was quite reasonable, and who can beat that beautiful view of Vancouver, and wonderful setting within Queen Elizabeth Park. Thank you very much Seasons for making our special day so wonderful!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Pleasantly surprised at the quality and value-for-money here.  Got the 3 course lunch menu and left very satisfied.

The steak was tender and flavorful.  The cake was quite substantial and rich.  The creme brulee had hints of citrus in it.

The mushroom soup was lacking a bit tho.  A bit bland, had to add some more salt and pepper to it myself but couldn't really help it.

Service was very good and the views are amazing on the patio.

featured_reviews.review_id:
We went to this restaurant for a family celebration:

The location was gorgeous, it is a very beautiful restaurant. You can't beat the view. The food was excellent, I would dare to say I chose probably the strongest pick on the menu  The halibut.

Desserts weren't impressive, but they were good.

They didn't get 5 stars based on service. The hostess was not very warm and at any point she didn't say please or thank you.

Our server was ok, he asked if there was a celebration and he brought a dessert on the house, it was nice.

I would still recommend this restaurant, it is a beautiful location and food was great to excellent. Not to mention the beautiful park beside it!

The service was absolutely amazing. Our server and the other staff were attentive without being over bearing. They were really communicative and amazing!

I loved their cocktails, their bread, the Caesar salad and their desserts. The main courses however were things you could find at any other restaurant with the same taste.

The view was outstanding, and you could see the city along with the Queen Elizabeth park. They have heaters in the patio section along with blankets. The restaurant seemed catered to older persons.

Main meals were priced at $20-$40.

places.address: Elika In Love, 416-2050 Scotia Street Buzz #136, Vancouver, BC V5T 4T1

featured_reviews.review_id:
This day would of not been complete without my dress.
After struggling to find anything different in wedding dresses I contacted Hrissa at Elika in Love. I had seen a picture of the dress I loved but it wasn't in stock. So I went in for a consultation to see what we could do.
Over 30 swatches of lace later I picked the lace I thought was pretty.
You can imagine how thrilled I was when it turned out to be stunning with tiny tasteful sequins, the perfect accent to my winter wedding.
Through my meetings with Hrissa she hand crafted the dress of my dreams. I never thought I'd get the "say yes to the dress" feeling but I couldn't stop smiling.
And on the day of my wedding I didn't want to take it off, stunning and comfortable.
I can't wait to have the reception so I can wear it again.

To be honest with you I've probably visited about 9 store before I came to this one and she was the nicest out of all those other bridal stores. I actually was eyeing another dress online and they didn't have it in stock to try. Hrissa, took the time to show me on a mannequin how the dress might look on me. Also the dresses she designs herself are just gorgeous, definitely visit this spot (very boho/New York fashion week!)! Her designs are just soooo dreamyyy

featured_reviews.review_id: I loved the dress that I bought from Elika in Love - it was flowy and perfect and fit like a dream. It was important to me during my wedding to work with designers who made beautiful things, particularly if they were involved in the process. So, on a trip to Vancouver I met Hrissa and ended up buying the first dress I tried on! It was lovely and perfect and looks as great in the photos as it felt to wear it. I also loved that I was able to get the dress in a colour that was verging on cream -- I have never felt really good wearing white or even ivory. And it matched the day and my husband's suit perfectly. Pro tip: Because if the train, the Athena works really well if you get married on a windy day.

Hrissa and her designs are so equally charming and beautiful. I went to her after seeing her "Elle" gown featured in a BC Wedding Magazine.
And I'm so glad I did!

Dresses are tried on in Hrissa's well-lit studio and it already feels like magic with the bright surroundings and personalized experience. Although professional, Hrissa is not precious with her designs and truly works with the wearer to tailor the dress to fit the married vision of the designer and the wearer. She's open to requests for custom tweaks, and makes recommendations when the need to be lead is evidenced.

If you're looking for a romantic dress and experience, Elika In Love is the perfect studio to do so. Thank you, Hrissa!

If you are looking for a CHANGE or NEED someone to give you motivation to work out, BLK Box gym is where you should head to right now.

Highly recommended 10/10

Everyone at the gym was kind and helpful especially my lovely trainer, Rachel. Rachel was tough at times, I used to call her evil, and very caring and attentive on the days I was feeling down. I enjoyed training with Rachel, I enjoyed the music she used to play for my sessions and I was very happy with the transformation I saw on my body after only 2 months of training. Also, I appreciate how Rachel was very understanding of my busy schedule and how she used to push me to keep coming to the sessions regularly. I am very happy with the results I achieved in the 6 months of training with Rachel and I would've continued working with her if I didn't have to move out of town. All the best Rachel :)

featured_reviews.review_id: I've been training with David for a few months and he changed my body in just 1 month. I was stunned to see how far I had come in such little time. I have known David for several years and his energy is infectious. I dealt with bloating, hypothyroidism and iron deficiency while doing shift work which all lead to a decline in my health. I went from almost 130lbs of "skinny fat" to 114lbs of muscle. He has helped me obtain the physique I've always wanted and the strength I never knew that I had. He's incredibly attentive, knowledgeable, and an overall genuine trainer and boxing coach.  His positive attitude and approachable nature makes me feel completely at ease. I cannot recommend David enough as he truly knows what he is doing and you will see how he genuinely cares about your goals. He radiates passion and dedication for his clients and I absolutely love training with him. He will make you succeed with your fitness goals. If you're seeking a trainer who will produce results and make you enjoy it at the same time - you have found the right place. My only regret is not starting with him sooner. I am so incredibly happy - Thank you David and the amazing Blk Box Team

featured_reviews.review_id:
I agree with the previous review author that I would also give zero stars.

I have been to this clinic since 2018. While my doctor is fantastic, the receptionists are extremely rude, impatient, and disrespectful, whether the communication is on the phone or in person.

My doctor only works on Tuesdays and Thursdays, and the clinic is supposed to take same-day appointments from 9 am -12 noon. I called to book an appointment with my doctor. The receptionist asked me what's the reason. I have been coughing for over a week and tested negative for COVID multiple times. Sometimes when I cough a lot, it is hard to breathe. The receptionist replied, "GO URGENT CARE!!" Then she hung up on me.

The worst interaction ever! No patients deserve to be yelled at when they feel ill and need care. I wanted to book an appointment because I did not want to go to urgent care and put extra pressure on the hospital. I want to save it for those who really need it. Health care is a public good. It is morally wrong for clinics to choose what patients to take. I agree with all the previous reviews that J-Von only wants your money. This clinic does not really care about your health.

My doctor is quitting soon, and I will not miss this clinic.

featured_reviews.review_id: We recently moved homes so we had to find a new vet in our area. I saw the reviews for Vancouver East Veterinary Walk-In Clinic so we booked our cat in here. Sadly, this was a huge mistake on our part. We took our cat in for her annual checkup. All of the documents were transferred from our previous vet to this one, so it should have her up to date vaccine information and other health background. Unfortunately, Dr. Shura didn't even pay attention to her vaccination history anyways, and despite our cat having gotten her 3-year vaccines in 2018, he said it was done in 2017 and then vaccinated her anyways. I didn't notice this until I got home and saw my previous invoices from the previous vet that said she last got the vaccination in 2018. A few days after we got home from the vet, my cat's hair started falling out in the area where the vaccination was injected. We tried calling Vancouver East Veterinary Walk-In Clinic on Wednesday at around 10AM and there was no pick-up (they are closed most of the week, open only for limited hours in the afternoon), no voice mail, and no emergency line you can call. We ended up having to drive back to our old vet to get her looked at because that was our only option. I understand that adverse side effect may happen after a vaccination, but I am very disappointed that the vet misread her vaccination history and gave her something she didn't need, and also we weren't able to reach them or an alternate number. When we were getting our cat looked at, Mr. Shura said to us that he doesn't like to overvaccinate animals because he'll get our money through teeth cleanings anyways (he had recommended a teeth cleaning for our cat). I couldn't tell if he was a vet or a used car salesman.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Difficult reception staff

I am a former patient here, and for more than a month I have been trying to get my records transferred so my new doctor can have them. I paid the fee to the records company that the office reception staff told me to contact for my records. I did not know at the time, but the company I was told to contact was completely incorrect. I paid a fee out-of-pocket to the incorrect company and have had to go through multiple rounds of back-and-forth with multiple people.

Now, my personal medical information is in the hands of a third-party that it should never have gone to and I have to pay even more money on top of what I already paid, to fix an error that is not my doing. When I called the clinic to report this issue, they admitted that it was their mistake, but did not apologize and essentially told me I was out of luck and would have to just solve it myself.

Utterly confused why this clinic would receive anything less than five stars. Convenient location on the upper floor of Marine Gateway Hub. Operates Monday to Friday. Lovely and professional staff who remain patient, helpful and composed during this unusually difficult time.

Our family is seen and treated by Dr Vasquez who has brilliant reviews on Rate My MD (not at all surprising). We have also seen Dr Cubra on occasion when Dr Vasquez has been away. Both doctors are incredibly patient, empathetic, and knowledgeable with relationships to other fantastic specialists in the community.

Dr Vasquez is hardly ever late for an appointment - sometimes he is a few minutes early. On the rare occasion I have waited an additional 5-10 minutes but this is a far departure from our previous GP. I can't believe had become accustomed to
waiting 1 hour + elsewhere.

When this clinic moved into our neighbourhood a few years ago, I happened to ask the receptionist which doctor I should see and they told me that ALL of them were amazing. We have happily found this to be true!

featured_reviews.review_id:
I cannot say enough good things about this clinic and I have recommended it to so many of my coworkers and friends!

Here's what I love the most:

- The interior design of the clinic is just beautiful. It feels very welcoming and is always super clean!

- All the ladies at the reception are so lovely, patient and helpful. I find their service always friendly and I never feel rushed when booking an appointment or asking a question, even though they are very busy!

- I use the walk-in clinic here and Dr. Cubra is absolutely amazing. He is the kindest doctor,  very patient, understanding, trustworthy and extremely knowledgeable. I never feel rushed and he always takes the time to listen to my symptoms and explain his recommendations. I truly believe he goes above and beyond for all the patients he sees. He has been an extremely huge help (especially this year) for me and I am so thankful for him and this clinic. The team at this clinic...they are the best!

- I have never felt I had to wait an unreasonable amount of time, which is amazing for a walk-in clinic. And if they feel I have, they always apologize which just shows how thoughtful they are.

Thank you so much, Marine Gateway MC. I so appreciate all you do for me and the other patients you see.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I have had tightness and pain in my left arm after my second vaccination for 4 months now.

I've gone to the chiropractor, acupuncture, massage therapists with no avail and after enduring this pain for 4 months, I already lost hope and figured life would be like this since I'm getting into my late 60's.

However after seeing Lester for Physio, in just 2 sessions I already feel 40% better!

I went from having limited mobility and no strength in my left arm to being able to go about my day normally now 

I highly recommend people to see Lester as he is very caring and skillful!

featured_reviews.review_id: Today I went and got another new kitten from Nikki. I went to her lovely home and met her cat crew. This is my second kitten from her in the last year. Just before Xmas last year my daughter and I got a little ginger girl and we love her so much we wanted to give her a friend.  Of course we went back to Nikki and she didn't let us down. Nikki briefly spoke of how some of these cats as well as dogs,  had been treated prior to her stepping in and rescuing them and about how the pandemic and natural disasters have increased the poor faith of these vulnerable animals.  She really cares for animals.  She is defiantly a cat lady through and through. The work she does for these animals is incredible. I don't know what will happen to all the animals in the b.c in distress when she retires. Although I can't see her retiring bc she cares too much about animals being treated badly. Weather it be an issue of hoarding, owners on substances and or natural disasters. As well as her program for seniors she is right on it. We often get caught up in our busy lives and  forget about animals and there well being.  If you can't adopt a cat from Nikki please consider sponsoring a cat or make a donation. I'm not sure if she excepts blankets and towels but that could be an idea as well.

This program of seniors for seniors is a big scam and financial and emotional  abuse of seniors.  I believed the video which promised to care for the health of the senior cat and all the senior had to do was love the cat.  From the first day Nikki's reluctance to care became evident.  The cat I was looking after was in poor health from the beginning.  Any time I called to get approval to go to the vet, Nikki would shriek at me saying he is "Just an old cat.  I'm going to have him euthanized."   The first time she said that, I left the cat at the vets certain he would be killed.  Five days later, the vet called me to pick him up.  I was in SHOCK.
Every occasion I had to deal with her was traumatizing and unpleasant!!  A horrible experience.  Abusive.
Uses pre-approval to get out of paying.  Stay away from this one. I spent over $3,000 in medical care on my own and she owes me $1500 from pre-approved vet visits which she refuses to pay.  All from the scam that the visits weren't pre-approved.  And how can anyone prove that one way or another?
This is cruelty .

Like many I missed the shared bathroom 'feature' on the Hotels.com site, but looking beyond that the host is very welcoming and the place is kept immaculately clean. Even my single room was spacious enough. The kitchenette comes well equipped with hob, fridge and microwave. Crockery and cutlery is also supplied. There's also a common kitchen upstairs. A TV in the room would have been preferred.

If you are a pedestrian then location could be a challenge.  Like many areas of Vancouver redevelopment is killing the local stores and supermarkets so you need to travel further. A 10 minute walk takes you to excellent transit options. A car would open up even more choice.

Not remotely accessible due to being an older home.

featured_reviews.review_id: I had a matrixectomy here for an ingrown toenail about a year ago. The podiatrist seemed very unsure of herself, which was a bit unsettling, but I decided to have the procedure done anyway because I just wanted it done and it's relatively simple. The room was very small and cramped, I'm not sure if the podiatrist has their own office. Because the office was small, the equipment seemed a bit disorganized. The procedure seemed to be done okay, the incisions seemed straight and I think the phenol was applied, but the ingrown toenail has returned. Everything about the experience was mediocre, and now I have to get the procedure done again anyway somewhere else.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I've been using The Maids service for years on and off. They have never once let me down or ever provided less than excellent service.

The team that shows up is always very professional, personable and kind. And dealing with Bruce or the assistant managers is always a pleasure. They are extremely accommodating to any needs I may have. For instance, I have two kittens, who started off with poor health. Working with Bruce and the team we tried different schedules or breaks and approaches that created a minimal stress environment for the cats, which mean everything to me.

In general, I try to stay up to date on cleaning myself, but after years of degrading back pain, knowing I can rely on The Maids to pick up my slack and keep my apartment looking amazing is a huge relief.

I'm extremely grateful when I come across businesses that deliver above and beyond expectations.

Thank you for years of quality service

featured_reviews.review_id:
Dr Sung mi Song is very rude and unprepared doctor. "Most time" I visited her she had wrong information about my medical records and it made me feel she was not prepared before meeting her patient. It seemed it didn't bother her at all.

During the meeting, she used to talk to me in an unpleasant way that she seemed she was very annoyed by me not understanding what she said. She probably thought I was a stupid. As a patient I was very discouraged to ask questions and I didn't feel like to keep conversation with her.

There WERE times She didn't called me on time, or met me when in-person meeting(which I understood since she could be busy). But she was very impatient and even aggressive when I couldn't received her call on time when I was really sick.
She called "7 times in a row" in total to me and my husband which I think is not necessary (she probably want us to receive the call so that she can yell) and said, we'd better find another dr if we keep doing this. It sounded almost like a threat. I wish I could recorded the phone call I had with her.

If you have a baby, don't take them to her since she seems she doesn't know how to treat with a little one. My baby was literally freaked out whenever getting a shot from her. It was horrible experiences as a parent, but since it's hard to find a dr so I kinda made compromise to keep her as my dr.

Now I regret myself being too patient with her and didn't find another dr more earlier.
Hopefully nobody had or will have experiences like me.

Not sure if anyone from the clinic is willing to talk to me but I want to let dr. Song to know that patients are not stupid, and not her emotional trashcan.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Long time patient of this clinic and the doctors here, but this one incident involving their reception staff was just appalling. Your reception staff must disclose to all patients that there is a $50 "no show fee" even for phone call appointments. To force someone to pay this fee after a phone call was missed for legitimate reasons ESPECIALLY when it was not disclosed upon booking is borderline robbing.

Please reconsider your policy surrounding phone vs. in-person appointments and/or re-train reception staff to be more considerate of patients circumstances. It seems they can greatly benefit from a lesson in using discretion. Not every patient visits the clinic frequently enough to see the notices for themselves. It is the job of the front desk receptionists to make policies transparent.

Such a shame to have encountered hostility from your staff after so so many years of being a patient (my entire life so far to be exact...). To expect us to constantly bend our equally busy schedules to fit into the odd schedules of all the doctors here is impractical and a quick way to lose patients. I am starting to think I am better off finding a different practice to seek health care. The current front desk team is truly mediocre at their job at best.

Edit: reply received and read. Unfortunately it missed to address the point about reception staff failing to disclose such an apparently important policy. Still not willing to admit wrongdoing?

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text:
Hello Kimberly,

We are very sorry for your experience. When our patients book appointments, we expect them to be committed to the time they booked. If our patients are unable to make it to the time they booked, they are welcome to call in and adjust their appointment 24 hours before their booked time. If our patients have an emergency or a legitimate reason, we usually waive the no show fee and end with a warning. Phone appointments are just as important as in-person appointments, which is why there is a no show fee for phone calls as well. If you still have any questions or concerns, please email us at info@forwardcaremedical.com and we will assist you the best of our abilities.

Thank you,
FCM

featured_reviews.review_id: I've been going to this busy clinic for several years. The doctors are pleasant and have good bedside manner. For urgent appointments, I've been fit in to an appointment same day or next day with my primary physician or another on duty physician that day. The front staff team is efficient. The clinic is quite busy most days, even during the pandemic, so expect a short wait before seeing your doctor.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Started to see Dr Amanda Lau before they expanded from a 2 doctors office. Too business type of services instead of a "caring practice".
No more than  2 questions allowed to ask  even if you have not seen them for so long!
The office is so crowded like a zoo!  I was put on hold with that terrible ding ding music every single call & you will be told that the next appointment will be a week later! I feel sorry for those sick elderly patients if they need quick assistance! Even worst is when the elderly don't even know how to book the appointment online! Terrible office management with too many doctors working for Dr Amanda Lau, the boss, who only works 2 days a week, few hours a day. Expecting the patients to accommodate her schedules so I requested to switch to one of her staff doctors but no spaces were reserved for us, the loyal patients! I will never come back to this office again!

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text:
Hello, we are very sorry about your experience. Unfortunately, we can only limit our patients to one or two concerns per appointment as there is a time restraint. If we allow our patients to go over the 10 minute limit, other patients would not be able to have their appointment on time. We do however encourage our patients to book multiple appointments if they have more concerns to discuss with our doctors.

If our patients require quick assistance, we do sometimes allow urgent same-day bookings. If you have any questions or concerns, please email us at info@forwardcaremedical.com and we will help you in the best way we can.

Thank you,
FCM

featured_reviews.review_id:
Great laundromat!
The owners are so friendly and nice!
Sadly there are hardly any laundromats left in Vancouver, and I hope they stay in business for many more years!
I get a family run business vibe, they are hard workers and they are always busy doing tons of drop off orders but I've never had an issue with needing a machine when I come in, have never had to wait even at busy times.
They run their business very efficiently and don't put up with shenanigans.
Everything takes loonies or quarters, but they will give you change at the till.
Largest washing machines are $7/load, and the dryers are very fast. Usually a big load will dry in 30 minutes and cost $2.50 ish.

Hi Ashley. So I'll explain why I'm asking you to wait. Basically I only take on 1 client in a day if it's a standard SMP Correction / or touch up. With people who have a large area or full scalp correction ( like yourself having alopecia) I want to give you / all my clients a high quality result and a quality SMP session. So I need 1 day free before your session and 1 day free after. I do this to keep my wrists fully rested and healed for each client. Most company's take on multiple clients in a day and they have you on a time clock. When they do this they just spread out your smp Pigmenting and keep asking you to come back in for more sessions(sometimes 4 to 6 sessions). But with my business, I want to try my best to get everyone done in 2 sessions. (90%) of my clients are done in 2 sessions. Because I take my time and again only take on 1 client in a day or every other day when doing large sessions. So you have me at my best rested self. I'm all about quality over quantity. I don't think its fair if I took multiple clients in a day. The second or third client wouldn't have me at my fully rested self. I put in 5000 to 15000 smp hair follicle replications on average per session. So my wrists need rest.

As for you, the LGBTQ community, Or any human being in this world. Your sexual orientation, race, mindsets, religions, or any personal things have nothing to do with Scalp Micropigmentation.  I'm here to help anyone in need of SMP of any backround I don't discriminate. Your scalp and getting you a good high quality SMP outcome is great for us all. It's good for business and also for you to be happy is my goal. So shoot me a text or email anytime and I'll book you in for when im fully rested so we can get you the result you want. Thanks

featured_reviews.review_id:
Support Our Troops both past and present.

When one considers with gratitude the freedoms which are enjoyed today in the culture that we have -  with the democracy that we hold dear to heart - its important to remember that we are living the legacy of giants who came before us.

This is the world that I wanted to leave for my children, one that is imperfect, yet strives to move towards an unilateral improvement for the good of this world, our species and our god. Some may see our modern day Legions or other gathering spots for veterans of war as bygone institutions. Places where you go to get a beer and a 50/50 ticket for a meat draw and that's it, but no.

Look beneath what is visible on the surface and what you see are old friends stitched together from the bonds of war, men and women who have seen inordinate levels of loss, yet are bound by their camaraderie and companionship to meet and greet each other despite the ongoing battles this world invariably succumbs to. This is what people miss.

So make your way down to the local arena of friendship. I highly recommend it.

featured_reviews.review_id: Highly recommend this eco/gastronomic tour. At 2+ hours, would make a great add-on to your day exploring beautiful Stanley Park. I rode my bike along the Seawall to the rendezvous point and added a wonderful 2nd Beach ocean swim at the end; a perfect way to experience the park for locals and visitors alike while also learning about BC West coast natural history and ecology. The feast on the beach was beyond my expectations: Dungeness  crab, smoked salmon, mussels, scallops, local wild mushrooms, sea asparagus and huckleberry tarts.  This tour would be a great idea for a foodie group, group birthday event or stagette/hen party.

What a horrible experience! I came in with what I thought was a screen replacement problem and a question about my phone slowing down. They took my phone to the back and opened it up without asking and replaced the battery and the screen. With a horrible after market screen that didn't fit and had horrible colour and was blurry.
I had specifically said I wanted to get a quote first before working on the phone. Two other people in line were coming back because their phones still weren't working properly after being fixed.
It was a nightmare I felt rushed and not listened to. The music was blaring.They charged me $500 dollars. I got home and the phone didn't work. They had made a big deal about throwing in a free screen protector but it was brittle plastic and when I dropped my phone on a thin carpet it broke and so did the screen. I always use a gel screen protector so this was ridiculous. Cheap cheap cheap! They refused to fix it so altogether I think I paid $700 for a phone that stopped working in less than a year. If you don't know much about electronics all of this is a bit daunting. I was recovering from an injury and wasn't very mobile. I didn't have the energy to shop around.I didn't know who to trust or what my options were.Buyer beware don't shop here!

featured_reviews.review_id:
A summary of my experience with this store over 5 consecutive days. For accessibility reason with my disability, I rely on the phone vibration to let me know that there's notification or a phone call, and I use the phone to text daily with haptic feedbacks on the keyboard, and whatnot.

Day 1:
Phone was working fine, including vibration and haptics. I was using the phone up to the last minute to browse the internet a bit while waiting, and the haptics were still working that time. My Pixel 5's battery capacity was low, so I decided to get a battery replacement at the store. I took the phone to the shop on Fraser Street, and was charged $110 and the warranty claims to repair all issues stemming from their repair.

I picked up the phone 5pm same day and I was told leave the screen alone after sealing. Later in the night when I think the screen glue's solid enough, I noticed the phone vibration wasn't working.

Day 2:
10am in the morning: I went back to the shop to fix the vibration because. The male employee who looked at the phone, checked the vibration setting, agreed that it isn't working, and said the phone can be ready for pick up around 5pm.
2pm: I checked with the store to see if the repair's been done. I was told it's in progress.
4pm: I was told was still being fixed, and it'd be fixed before the store closes at 8pm.
730pm: Tried calling them several times between 6pm to 7pm, and I didn't get a phone call back from them, so I went to the store and found it already closed.

Day 3:
There was no communication from them for the whole day despite calling them to ask and getting voice mail. When I went to the store, my phone still had its screen removed. I was also told that the senior technician would come in the morning the next day, that it'll be fixed by 3pm tomorrow.

Day 4:
I went to the store at 3pm. My phone's vibration didn't work when picked up, had the setting looked through by the front desk employee. She confirmed that there's no settings. However, she also refused to accept that the battery replacement caused the vibration issues. As of midnight, the phone still had no vibration.

Day 5:
I went in again, and the same female employee went through the vibration test app and all the settings, and so did the older guy with glasses. However, they were insistent that the battery replacement didn't cause the vibration.

When I asked the lady how are they sure that they didn't cause the damage. She claimed that their technicians "know everything". After a while they had the technician to come and talk to me again. When I asked the technician himself what's the problem with the vibration motor, he said didn't know why and that maybe my phone's been like this before I came to them.

The technician claimed that they do not touch the vibration motor at all so it couldn't have been their fault. He wrote that they can't open the phone again because the screen might break, even though the Gorilla Glass screen can withstand 500C easily. He added that if I take responsibility for the screen they can do it for a "little charge" of $30. And stresses that phone screens are very expensive.

It sounded like an insinuation an accident would happen to my phone if I kept pushing for warranty repair. For him to do his job, he'd have to remove the screen from every phone to do his work. For someone who does his daily work around phones, he lacked confidence in himself, otherwise he wouldn't ask clients responsible for the cost of broken glass screen and charge the more for extra repairs. Therefore, by asking me to take responsibility for the cost of the screen in case he damages it, he's being honest about his lack of ability (or care) to fix my problem. And that they won't cover a screen broken due to their own repairs.

As such, it's best to take the technician's advice to heart and not go to Fix 4 U Cellular and that there are more professional, competent, ethical, and knowledgeable cell phone repair shops elsewhere.

Dr. Michelle Lin is my mom's and my family doctor. She is patient, genuine, punctual, efficient, and goes the extra mile to ensure we clearly understand the issues and applicable next steps.

I also had a blood test yesterday and I did not schedule a follow-up appointment. I was pleasantly surprised that Dr. Lin called me today to go through my results together with me!

We are both very thankful and appreciative of her wonderful care :)

featured_reviews.review_id:
I chose the Forward Care East Clinic for my mother in law as its close to where she lives, the doctor is caring (Dr Jeffrey Lau) and the reception staff is very efficient.

Pre-Covid, when my mother in law had some dizzy episodes on a Saturday, we call the office, they fit her in with another doctor in the office and follow up with a letter to Emergency.

Currently, they do either phone appointments or in office appointments and most times when we are in the phone appointment, if the doctor needs to see what is concerning (a rash, take blood pressure, etc.), they do their best to find time to let you come in, luckily for us it was within the same day.

They referred my mother in law for a geriatrician, and Dr Zhang is also located in the same office. Very efficient in communication and coordination. Before the Geriatrician appointment, the staff called us twice with reminders. I appreciate the calls and reminders.

The online booking is the only negative. We get email notification to book for flu shots, etc but our doctor was not set up, or won't allow on the booking site.  Most times it doesn't work, so best to call the office.

The report appeared to take forever to be completed (Mar 2022 - Jan 2023) but through no fault of Michaels. We are a self managing complex so many questions needed to be addressed through adapting new bylaws which directly affected the depreciation report.  Michael was with us every step of the way to answer questions or direct us to the proper authority to get interpretation. He always answered emails promptly and shed light on any concerns we might have had. Michael presented a zoom meeting to our unit owners to clarify the depreciation report and answer questions  which greatly simplified council's position.
So without hesitation we can recommend NLD Consulting as a firm that truly does care about their client.

After having ordered from Karakoram multiple times in the past, this will be our last.

The taste was decent for everything we ordered, but the amount of oil that's dripping from the food - One meal is enough to clog your arteries.

Never again, I would highly recommend not ordering from them. There are far better restaurants in the city that offer amazing Pakistani dishes thats not soaking in cooking oil.

The 1 star for taste only, stripping 4 others for the amount of grease you have to fight through to get to the actual food.

The rest of the dishes were alright, papad, naan, Kheer, and I liked the carrot pickles.

featured_reviews.review_id:
This place is a classic Filipino restaurant serving authentic and traditional Filipino dishes with many choices. The foods are outstanding at a reasonable price. One of my favorites is their signature dish "Crispy Pata" which I always order for takeout. Very crispy and cooked to perfection which is completely paired with their signature vinegar dipping sauce. They also serve various desserts such as halo-halo (sweet shaved ice dessert with various toppings), Turon ( sweet banana-jackfruit spring roll), Buko Pandan (coconut and pandan flavored gelatin with cream and sweetened milk), and a lot more.

The place also features decor and ambiance, reflecting Filipino culture with Filipino music playing in the background. Plus, they have a very friendly, welcoming, and pretty staff. This is a must-try restaurant that tastes like Home. If you miss Pinoy foods or want to try authentic Filipino cuisine, this place is for you.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Disclaimer :
I have personally not stayed at this location, however recently my friends who were visiting from Ontario, booked this place and this is based on their feedback.

Awesome location, friendly staff, open setting for rooms, all on the ground level.
Rooms were clean and service staff was very helpful.

The major drawback is that each room does not necessarily have a small microwave, or fridge. So if you have kids, you need to choose the kitchenette option when booking.

Less than 15ins walk from the Nanaimo and 29th Avenue skytrain stations which is a blessing, transit bus service also available as it falls on the Major Kingsway road.

places.address: Wally's Burgers, 2661 E 49th Ave, Vancouver, BC V5S 1J9

featured_reviews.review_id:
Came here especially today to use my Patty Pass and tried the Veggie Deluxe Burger with cheese. It was sooo good. The sauce was the best part.
I also have to comment on the prices. It's so affordable. Half the price of most places nowadays. A can of beer is 3.75! My burger (no sides) was 6.75. Unheard of these days!
The service was fast and friendly. When I walked in I was the only customer but shortly after it filled up.
I'll definitely be back when I'm in the area!

Got home and discovered the fries were soggy, stuck together and a dark brown colour.  Not yellow, crispy fries you expect from a burger joint. I have been going to Wally's Burger since the Kingsway days.
They just lost Wally as a client.  Will be posting in my social accounts about the terrible food.

places.name: Fraserview Banquet Hall
places.address: Fraserview Banquet Hall, 8240 Fraser St, Vancouver, BC V5X 3X6

featured_reviews.review_id:
I'd like to give a huge thank you to Fraserview Hall for going above and beyond to host my Haldi and Reception events. Working with Fraserview was extremely easy and the staff prioritize their customers and truly want you to have the best experience.

The hall itself is a stunning venue with chandeliers throughout the hall, a massive elevated dancefloor, modern carpeting, high quality speaker system and a gorgeous outdoor balcony that my guests enjoyed majority of their evening taking pictures outside on a sunny day.

I can't thank the Manager Antony enough for his exceptional customer service. He is solely the reason why I booked both of my events at Fraserview Hall. I had other deposits at another competing hall but Antony ensured me that I was in good hands and now that my events are over I can 1000% say that Fraserview Hall exceeded my expectations. My family and friends are now booking Fraserview Hall for their events after attending mine. It was the most glamorous Haldi and Wedding Reception I've ever experienced and booking Fraserview Hall was the best decision!

The in house DJ was wonderful and played beautiful songs that my guests and myself could dance all night to. I highly recommend booking the in house DJ, they are very organized and prepare all your songs to make sure everything runs smoothly.

The food was absolutely delicious, my guests had second helpings and several people told me their favourite items were the vegetable chow mein, fish pakora, chicken tikka, goat curry and bbq tandoori chicken.

I also really enjoyed working with the Decor team. They truly worked their magic and made every detail look absolutely perfect. My Haldi night looked like a Bollywood movie set with all the beautiful bright colours, umbrella arch, glittery table runners, gold elephants and fancy decor pieces.

They also created the most stunning set up for my Reception which included a hanging floral and crystal walkway, floating candles, chandeliers, white roses with an elegant backdrop for the stage. They upgraded and sourced gorgeous decor and took care of everything. I am grateful for the hard working staff, especially Harmeet and Shrungerri who executed my visions and made them better! My advice to anyone booking Fraserview Hall is to trust the staff, they know what they are doing and you will not be disappointed.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Installation was decent overall, but they messed up one of the rooms and had to cover it up with awkward looking panels near the edges where the floor ends at floor-to-ceiling windows.

Other issues:
- Original expectations were that they would do the kitchen flooring as well. But they bailed on doing the entire floor because of some custom cabinetry that is raised above the flooring on elevated stilts. So half of the kitchen flooring is incomplete (old flooring hidden under the cabinetry). Would have been much better to be up front about that at the beginning.

- They promised to replace our baseboards, but during the renovations they said the original baseboards were fine and asked if they would just use those. We ask for them to go ahead with new ones thing they would do the full job. Instead they cut new baseboards without painting them properly and never added caulking. So we were left to do that our selves.

- They messed up one of our closet doors (couldn't get it to fit back in) so they cut it. Now the one door doesn't match the height of the other.

Overall, a lot of the issues could have been prevented with better communication on their part before and during the project. They also rushed at the end to finish up. We offered to give them more time, but they already had other projects waiting to go right afterwards.

Then a fellow came in an he had a tire with him, Randy dealt with him his tire was whisked away into the garage and he sat in the waiting area with me and one other fellow

At that time the fellow (customer) who was dealt with ahead of me even though I came in before them was speaking to me and I had said It has been 37 minutes since he asked me to have a seat. The other customer said ring the bell and I said, he knows I am here, he told me to have a seat for a moment and I have been here for 20 minutes before you came in, he knows I am here.

Randy then comes toward the waiting area and interrupts our conversation with a question what about was said about the bell on the desk. I said I was speaking with this gentleman. featured_reviews.review_text:
I have to say that Randy Sokalofsky the  Owner/Manager @ The Big O Tire on Kingsway in Vancouver is not interested in keeping a customer or even trying to be professional when you value your time. I will not take him my car care needs again.

I came into the shop at 10:58 AM, I know because I looked at my phone, I was busy and was watching the time carefully. Randy said hi and asked me what I was in for. I said a tire with a not so slow leak. Randy then said have a seat.

While waiting in the lobby of his messy little shop he was taking payment from a customer named "Jodie" they talked about his and her children, grand children and her career working with children. That was a 12 minute conversation. Then a fellow came in an he had a tire with him, Randy dealt with him his tire was whisked away into the garage and he sat in the waiting area with me and one other fellow

Randy went into the back of the shop, came out, sat at his desk and while using the computer took out a plastic food container and fork and began eating a bit. He then went back into the garage area at back of the shop.

At that time the fellow (customer) who was dealt with ahead of me even though I came in before them was speaking to me and I had said It has been 37 minutes since he asked me to have a seat. The other customer said ring the bell and I said, he knows I am here, he told me to have a seat for a moment and I have been here for 20 minutes before you came in, he knows I am here.

Randy then comes toward the waiting area and interrupts our conversation with a question what about was said about the bell on the desk. I said I was speaking with this gentleman. Randy then says well you are arguing about the bell. I said Randy no one is arguing about anything and the conversation was between me and the man I was speaking with. I said you ask me to wait a moment and have a seat then 37 minutes later the thing you want to address / say to me is to interrupt a casual conversation with another and characterize it as arguing and not to ask how can you help me?

I said there is no problem waiting but if you knew that it would be 40 minutes before you would even speak to me why would you not value my time and tell me that, why not tell me you will be taking other customers before me, doing working on your computer and having something to eat, please come back later or call / book online.

after I asked that Randy then told me to get out of the shop and don't come back...

He then nastily said and pick up your coffee off the table and get out. I said I have not come here to take orders from you, how can you be so rude?

He then said fine don't leave. I said really you are going to try to play mind games with a paying customer and try to use reverse psychology. I mentioned what I do in mental heath and he scoffed and laughed right in my face as he mockingly says "psychologist".

He then kept on being rude and following me out the door, I said you wasted 37 minutes of my time already, he then says "it is 39 minutes" now and called me a broken person who could not be helped...
featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text:
The video recording demonstrates how foolish you acted and how the others waiting around you laughed at you after you left (in case you have the ability to self-reflect). One person, with a head-shake of disbelief, pitied the 'beneficiaries' of your psychological work. Now I'm seeing the irony in how a person trained to understand humankind can't wrap his mind around a simple concept of 'waiting one's turn - no babysitting required' & 'complaining as a way to force entitlement on others'.

There was also discussion about how you openly usurped the authority of God Almighty in your feeble attempt at bullying as if 'the powers had been vested in you' or some other silly nonsense. We don't tolerate such behavior so when you began attacking, accusing, and displaying prejudice... ya, you're going to have to leave. Permanently.  Discrediting Christianity by representing it horribly is a symptom of something quite negative.

CLARIFICATION: you as a no-appointment drop-in were assured that we would be able to assist you in repairing a tire without having to leave it and return (unlike the other shops you tried). The shop was informed that you (a drop-in tire repair) were waiting to have your tire repaired. The shop (not me as I'm not the person in the back doing the tire repairs (as you erroneously concluded)) continued with the work that was booked before you while I, doing my part, ensured that the shop ran smoothly. I also took payment/invoiced a customer who's vehicle was completed, had a conversation with a customer as part of my lunch-break, and spent a couple minutes actually eating my lunch and replying to emails. I think the rest of your utter misconstrued blah blah blah above demonstrates the rest of the story.

Complaining to others who were waiting then denying when I overheard and attempted to explain was also immature.

We don't like people who berate/belittle service industry people. We don't like people who place themselves above their neighbours. We don't like people who are openly judgmental. And we don't like people who bring negativity (toxicity) into our space. You are all of these things. Standing up and blurting out - as some type of qualifier - that you are a psychologist so you know Randy is wrong sealed the deal.

Enjoy your life. Enjoy the ramifications of the path you've justified taking. Enjoy blessing another shop in Vancouver with your superiority complex. We all enjoyed the relief and peace that was restored after you stomped off like a child. Our world is better without you.

Blessings & buh-bye.

I hope they continue to provide excellent fries without compromising the quality for speeding up the process.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I went during a non-peak time so there was no line-up. I agree with the other reviews that it takes quite a while to get your order.

My order: Sour Cream & Onion Loopy Fries (size: Mega)
I really liked how it wasn't greasy at all. It's like a hybrid between fries and chips. The seasoning was great, not overly salty (had a hint of sweetness to balance the flavour), and evenly coated as well. Very crispy, and stays crispy - no sogginess even at the bottom.

Process: They take your order, and then you wait for your fries to come out of this (air fryer-like?) machine - which takes a while, then they dump the fries into a tray, scoop them back up to throw them in a bucket to shake with seasoning (by hand), then throw them BACK on ANOTHER tray after seasoning, then scoop them up into your bucket/bag. Seems tedious, but I assume they have their reasons as they're a huge chain and very popular in Asia.

Kevin at Mr. Rooter then referred us to BC Preferred Restoration to do major repairs in the basement suite. The floor, dry wall and cabinets had to be replaced as they were all contaminated by sewer water. Steve in the head office guided as expertly through the insurance maze. He was responsive and professional. Ivan's work was top notch and we are very pleased with the end product.

Mr. Rooter and BC Preferred Restoration took a horrible nasty incident and made it tolerable with a timely professional approach. 5Star experience.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Review: Rob James - Masterful SMP Experience

Rob James is a true master at what he does. From the moment I met him, his ability to clearly communicate all the details and process involved made the entire experience enjoyable. He took the time to patiently explain every aspect of the Scalp Micropigmentation (SMP) procedure, ensuring that I had a thorough understanding of what to expect. His professionalism and passion for his work were evident throughout, instilling confidence in his abilities.

During the SMP process, Rob's attention to detail and precision were remarkable. He carefully considered factors such as hairline design, color matching, and shading, ensuring that the results would look natural and seamlessly blend with my existing hair. The final outcome exceeded my expectations, and I couldn't be happier with the results. Rob's talent for creating realistic and flawless SMP results is truly impressive.

Aside from his exceptional skills, Rob's friendly and approachable demeanor made the entire experience even more enjoyable. We spent several hours chatting during the sessions, and it felt like spending time with a friend rather than a professional. His ability to make me feel comfortable and at ease was genuinely appreciated.

If you're looking for a skilled SMP practitioner who can deliver outstanding results while making the process enjoyable, look no further than Rob James.

Having to walk over to find a closed branch on Monday when I definitely needed to do a face to face meeting is very frustrating.  Sure there are other Vancity branches open, but now I need to drive my gasoline powered car to another branch further away is definitely not good to the environment!

featured_reviews.review_id:
I've been wanting to visit this place for a while now, and today I was in the neighborhood and saw that it was opening at 7, so I got there just before they opened, and it was still dark. I saw them going into the cafe and many of the employees of the supply store they are located at. Had no idea it was at a lumber and hardware supply warehouse, surrounded by many other commercial warehouses, such a great surprise, which just makes it that much better. Absolutely loved the atmosphere and the owners. Very friendly older couple and their son run this awesome famiky owned cafe.

Awesome home cooked breakfast, amazing friendly and relaxed service, and unbelievable atmosphere. When I got there, I was the only one, but I still loved it so much. The old school diner style furniture and music were awesome. I got the pancake with blueberries, sunny side up eggs, and sausage, which were all very good. Loved their old small glass coffee maker and the mugs. The son who was serving was very nice and friendly....he me told me that this place has been around since the 1940s and his parents got this place 15 years ago have been in the business for so long after they retired, wanted to have a slow and small place and now this place is exploded and is crazy busy ...which I find very funny and awesome.

Will definitely come back to try their burgers and Chinese food.

featured_reviews.review_id:
After hearing so much about Northern Cafe, my anticipation was high as I finally made a reservation to dine at this much-acclaimed establishment. The decision to reserve a table proved to be wise; we were seated almost immediately upon arrival, avoiding the long wait times that had deterred us during a previous attempt to dine here.

Don't be fooled by it's surprising location or the state of the building (which might seem to some as if it were about to collapse at any moment).  Inside is something you won't find anywhere else in Vancouver!

The atmosphere at Northern Cafe is inviting, reflecting its family-run ethos. The menu offers a variety of comfort food options, and we opted for burgers and a side of poutine. The food was exceptional--each bite of the burger was a blend of flavors and textures, and the poutine was a delightful mix of crispy fries, cheese, and well-balanced gravy.

What stood out, even more, was the service. The staff were attentive and courteous, enhancing the overall dining experience. It's evident why this establishment has garnered such high praise and even topped lists of the best places to eat in Canada.

A particularly charming touch was the inclusion of watermelon slices with our meal. It added a refreshing contrast to the hearty fare and demonstrated the restaurant's attention to detail. Another delightful aspect was the handwritten reviews by children displayed on the wall, which actually helped us make our menu choices.

Northern Cafe lives up to its reputation. The combination of delicious food, excellent service, and a welcoming atmosphere makes it a must-visit. Making a reservation is highly recommended!

featured_reviews.review_id: This is a small and humble eatery, with many comforting dishes on the menu. The place is known for soup dumplings, pan fried dumplings, and spicy beef noodle soup. These are the three things I usually order. Noodles and dumplings are fresh tasting each time. Soup is just the right amount of spicy, and I like the beef. There isn't much sit down capacity, so be prepared to wait in line during prime times. Interior is what you'd expect from a small and authentic Asian eatery.

Lined up for 20 mins at the door (without shade ) to get in
The place is small and crowded with friendly staff
XLB was excellent very juicy and soupy
Wonton dumpling was ok with more veggie than meat but the dumpling wrapper was so  smoothy tasty! It suppose to come with 10 pcs but they gave me 9 first and told me one more coming and I appreciate their honesty
Portion of spicy noodle was quite small with a few pieces of meat only
The worse is the green onion pancake, dry, tasteless , hard and look aged
Overall with this price range for Shanghai food definitely worth a try!

featured_reviews.review_id: Arrived on a Sat evening and there was about a 20-30 min wait. Even though this place is very popular, I've been to other places that serve Chinese noodle dishes that are just as good at a similar price point. Don't get me wrong, the food was good, but for how busy and popular the place was, I expected slightly better. All in all, good food, but not mind blowing in which I would frequently patronize the place.

featured_reviews.review_id:
My family only waited about 5 minutes for a table on a weekday lunch. As soon as you get seated they give you menus and tea. Make sure you bring cash, cash only restaurant.

Soup dumplings were amazing! I have had zhajiang mian before and didn't like it but the one from here was really good. I also know a lot of people who like dan-dan noodles and they were indeed good but I found a bug in it and it turned me off. While eating the wait for tables grew with multiple people waiting and lined up outside.

featured_reviews.review_id: By far the best soup dumplings I have ever had! I always have to order another order because they are that good! You also know it's gonna be good when you can see them make them the dumplings right in front of you! I have been here many times already and their food does not disappoint. I got the Steamed Pork Buns (Xiao Long Bao/Soup Dumplings), Pan Fried Pork Buns, Pan Fried Dumplings and Beef Roll! I would recommend everything because it was really affordable and yummy. The soup from the Steamed and Fried Pork Buns was really flavourful! The Pan Fried Dumplings had a lot of filling and isn't like other dumplings I've had at other restaurants (which are sometimes frozen). You have to get the Beef Roll, I love the amount of meat, cucumbers and sauce there is in it! Another thing I like is how they have chili oil and vinegar at the table for you! I can't wait to come back and try their noodles and wontons,unfortunately it was too hot for that today.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Everything that I have tried here were amazing except for their dan-dan noodle which seemed a bit ordinary to me.

My favourite dish that I ordered would be their beef roll. Since their menu didn't have any images nor descriptions, I was left to imagine what this beef roll might be and surprisingly, it tasted amazing. I didn't expect it to be fried and if I didn't know it, the taste actually reminded me of peking duck.

This place accepts cash only so make sure to have cash on hand.
